name: Persis Khambatta -- Indian Actress/Model (Star Trek TMP "Lt. Ilia")
description:
Actress/Model Persis Khambatta

This is a textual inversion of actress/model Persis Khambatta, best known for her role as the bald-headed Deltan navigator in Star Trek: The Motion Picture. She was born in Bombay, India, and was Miss India in 1965. She also had roles in movies such as Nighthawks and The Wilby Conspiracy (with Michael Caine and Sydney Poitier). She is also distinguished as the first Indian female performer to present an award at the Oscars.

I have to say I have a LOT of satisfaction finally posting this TI. I've always thought Persis was a hauntingly beautiful and sexy woman -- sadly, she passed away fairly early in life in the late 1990s. Her beauty remains with us however in a form such as this.

I'm especially glad that this TI came out to my satisfaction (and hopefully yours) as the source material for her imagery is often low resolution or in black and white. I sourced imagery from screencaps of The Wilby Conspiracy (where she has a suspenseful scene as a sexy dental assistant with Sydney Poitier), as this is where I thought she looked absolutely alluring. After a number of tries ending up with monstrosities, I finally was able to get the right settings and training to get some lovely generation going.

Let me know how you like this TI. I might give yet another go at a V2 later, or learn to do LoRAs and then try that.
